Activity: A3 – Discover security concepts used in your house

Objective
The goal of this activity is to observe and analyse security concepts used on campus.

Method
I walked around my house and identified security measures such as CCTV cameras.

Findings
I discovered the following security implementations:
1. CCTV cameras - to record evidence in case of an incident
2. WiFi network password - to prevent outsiders from using the WiFi
3. Digital main door lock - an extra layer of protection that requires a digital code to open the first main door

Security Principle
These systems support confidentiality, integrity, and availability.

Reflection
This activity helped me understand how security concepts are applied in real environments.
